{"id":13076,"date":"2024-02-07T03:01:20","date_gmt":"2024-02-07T03:01:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/?p=13076"},"modified":"2024-02-20T23:15:26","modified_gmt":"2024-02-20T23:15:26","slug":"the-partnership","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/the-partnership\/","title":{"rendered":"The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies: &#8220;COVID-19, Here To Stay,  We Failed.&#8221;"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-container-4 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-3 wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-2 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-1 wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-7 wp-block-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-container-5 wp-block-column\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-twitter wp-block-embed-twitter\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">COVID-19, Here to Stay, we failed.<br><br>Ending the <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/COVID?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#COVID<\/a> Emergency is a <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/Disaster?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Disaster<\/a> for <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/Disabled?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#Disabled<\/a> People <br>Decisionmakers declaring that the loss of 400+ of our people per day does not rise to the level of being an emergency. <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/0YG9jvGZuR\">https:\/\/t.co\/0YG9jvGZuR<\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/WHO?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@WHO<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/CDCgov?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@CDCgov<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/WhiteHouse?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@WhiteHouse<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/0pgyPNQ6Uv\">https:\/\/t.co\/0pgyPNQ6Uv<\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/t.co\/qELASUs3lz\">pic.twitter.com\/qELASUs3lz<\/a><\/p>&mdash; The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies (@disasterstrat) <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/disasterstrat\/status\/1654987838310555655?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">May 6, 2023<\/a><\/blockquote><script async src=\"https:\/\/platform.twitter.com\/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"><\/script>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-container-6 wp-block-column\">\n<p>The disability forward response team <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/disasterstrategies.org\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/disasterstrategies.org\/\" target=\"_blank\">The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies<\/a> tweeted on May 6th, 2023 in response to the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/WHO\/status\/1654477334139863041\/photo\/1\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/WHO\/status\/1654477334139863041\/photo\/1\" target=\"_blank\">World Health Organization&#8217;s announcement<\/a> of the end of the global health emergency of COVID-19. As disaster responders, they write that &#8220;Ending the <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/COVID?src=hashtag_click\">#COVID<\/a> Emergency is a <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/Disaster?src=hashtag_click\" target=\"_blank\">#Disaster<\/a> for <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/hashtag\/Disabled?src=hashtag_click\" target=\"_blank\">#Disabled<\/a> People.&#8221; Removing COVID from the list of global health emergencies allows people to stop practicing habits that are crucial for protecting the disabled people around them. The <a href=\"https:\/\/disasterstrategies.org\/ending-the-covid-emergency-is-a-disaster-for-disabled-people\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"https:\/\/disasterstrategies.org\/ending-the-covid-emergency-is-a-disaster-for-disabled-people\/\">tweet&#8217;s linked article<\/a> states that &#8220;To the degree that precautions are being taken, these efforts will diminish when the Public Health Emergency is no longer in effect&#8221;. The graphic image represents the failures of the Biden Administration to protect people from the virus that is still rampant as &#8220;roughly 400 people still die from the virus each day&#8221;.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/disasterstrategies.org\/about-us\/\">The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies (The Partnership)<\/a>: &#8220;prioritizes equity, access, disability rights, disability justice, and full inclusion of people with disabilities, older adults, and people with access and functional needs before, during, and after disasters and emergencies&#8221;. They often focus on natural disasters and their impact on disability but also focus on international crises like COVID and other threats to public health and human\/civil rights. The training and education created by The Partnership has allowed for remote access to disaster information and response resources. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>-Stephanie Farmer<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The disability forward response team The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies tweeted on May 6th, 2023 in response to the World Health Organization&#8217;s announcement of the end of the global health emergency of COVID-19. As disaster responders, they write that &#8220;Ending the #COVID Emergency is a #Disaster for #Disabled People.&#8221;&hellip; <a class=\"continue\" href=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/the-partnership\/\">Continue Reading<span> The Partnership for Inclusive Disaster Strategies: &#8220;COVID-19, Here To Stay,  We Failed.&#8221;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":13077,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"advanced_seo_description":"","jetpack_seo_html_title":"","jetpack_seo_noindex":false,"_FSMCFIC_featured_image_caption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_nocaption":"","_FSMCFIC_featured_image_hide":""},"categories":[44],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/000-covid-here-to-stay.jpeg?fit=1080%2C1080&ssl=1","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13076"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/4"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=13076"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13076\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":13092,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/13076\/revisions\/13092"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/13077"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=13076"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=13076"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=13076"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}